= Abstract

OopsMate is a chess engine and research workbench implemented in Rust. The project investigates how classical search and evaluation techniques affect engine strength and efficiency by implementing features incrementally and benchmarking each release against its predecessor. The artefact is split into a main UCI engine crate and supporting crates for move-generation primitives and utilities, with an additional NNUE inference crate for neural evaluation integration. This report documents the project motivation, background literature, chosen methodology, tooling, artefact design, and an initial evaluation plan.

