== Academic Question

How do different techniques involved in chess programming affect a chess engine's playing strength and efficiency?

== Scope and Limitations

This project focuses on a CPU-based engine using classical search (alpha-beta family) and both handcrafted and NNUE-based evaluation. It does not attempt to reproduce self-play reinforcement learning systems (e.g., AlphaZero-style training) due to compute requirements, nor does it attempt to solve chess end-to-end. Benchmarks are constrained by available hardware, time controls, and opponent selection.

