= Project Methodology

The project adopts an incremental, experiment-driven development approach: each major technique is implemented as a distinct version so its effect can be measured. This suits chess engine development because the problem domain is well-defined (rules and correctness criteria are fixed), while performance and strength improvements emerge from iteratively adding and tuning optimizations.

For task-level management, a Kanban board supports continuous tracking of implementation work, bug-fixing, and experiments. For report-level planning, milestones align to larger deliverables (baseline engine, search/evaluation upgrades, benchmarking and documentation, final integration and write-up). This hybrid approach provides structure without constraining iterative exploration.

